📍Gordes, France

The prettiest village in France. The village has a colourful history, having survived the plague, earthquakes and bombings during wars. The history of this place is just fascinating, one of the castles here was built in 1031, insane!! Definitely add this place to your “must visit” in France 🫶🏽

Long promised Uruguay post with reccs ✨

We stayed at Jose Ignacio, magical place, similar vibes to st Tropez, a lot of beach restaurants, but more chill atmosphere. 

People live on a different time here that we are used to, waking up at 12, lunch at 3-4pm, dinner at 10🥲 you get used to that pretty fast 

Restaurants:
La Susana - absolute fav, great food & people. Amazing views and good spot to meet people. 
La Huella - food & vibes 
Chiringito - great for lunch, more chill, beach vibes 
Mostrador - incredible for lunch, prob the best food I’ve had in José 
Marismo - order steak 😮‍💨
Rizoma - breakfast place inside the library, their salmon toast was outstanding

Another day in the paradise 🐢🐳🩵🏝️
